    <goal>Create docs/architecture/wizard-framework-architecture.md — document the shared wizard framework, its 7 solution implementations, step management, and AI pre-fill integration</goal>
    <context>The Spaarke platform uses a shared wizard framework (WizardDialog component) that provides multi-step form workflows across 7 different solutions. The framework supports step navigation, validation, AI-assisted pre-fill of form fields, and customizable layouts. No architecture document captures this framework end-to-end.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-architecture skill structure
      - Source ALL content from actual code — do not invent wizard features
      - Document the shared WizardDialog component API and step management
      - Inventory all 7 solution-specific wizard implementations
      - Map AI pre-fill integration: how AI populates wizard fields from document analysis
      - Document step lifecycle: mount, validate, navigate, submit
      - Cite source files for framework and every implementation
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
